All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ErrorScreen
ErrorScreen is an activity class that represents an error page in the application.
FriendsAdapter
Adapter for the RecyclerView used on the Social Screen to display the user's list of friends
LoginActivity
An activity class for the Login Screen, used to handle logic so the user can enter their login information and attempt to login.
MatchesScreen
The screen used to display the restaurants the user has been matched with
Restaurant
Represents a restaurant with various details such as name, categories, location, etc.
Restaurant.Category
Represents a category of a restaurant.
Restaurant.Coordinates
Represents geographical coordinates with latitude and longitude.
Restaurant.Location
Represents a location with address details and geographical information.
RestaurantAdapter
Adapter for the RecyclerView to display a list of liked restaurants.
RestaurantProfileActivity
The Restaurant Profile screen, used to display a specific Restaurant's information
SignUpActivity
The Sign-Up screen; The user can enter their account information here and request to sign-up to Dinder
SocialActivity
The Social Screen displays the user's friends list, allows the user to invite friends to their group, and allows the user to send friend requests to other users.
UserHomeActivity
The Home Screen is considered the default location of the app.
UserProfileActivity
The User Profile screen, used to display the user's information and allow them to modify their dietary preferences and other settings affecting the rest of the app.
VolleySingleton
VolleySingleton using Android Volley to manage HTTP Requests being sent to and from the Springboot Server
WebSocketListener
Interface defining methods for handling WebSocket events.
WebSocketManager
Singleton WebSocketManager instance used for managing WebSocket connections in the Android application.
